1. Definitions

Software
The Open-Label Digital Product Passport software and any derivative works.

Digital Product Passport (DPP)
Any digital representation of product lifecycle, sustainability,
compliance, traceability, or product information generated, processed,
or displayed by the Software.

Interface
Any web page, API response, mobile application view, embedded widget,
or other user-facing display that renders or provides access to a
Digital Product Passport.

Derivative Work
Any modification, adaptation, extension, or fork of the Software.

Service Deployment
Running the Software as part of a service accessible over a network.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Grant of Rights

Subject to the terms of this License, you are granted a worldwide,
non-exclusive, royalty-free license to:

• Use the Software for any purpose
• Copy and distribute the Software
• Modify the Software
• Run the Software as a network service
• Create derivative works
• Use the Software commercially

---------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Source Code Availability (Network Copyleft)

If you modify the Software and deploy it as part of a service accessible
over a network, you must make the complete corresponding source code of
your modified version available to users of that service.

The source code must include:

• all modifications
• build scripts
• configuration files required to reproduce the running system

The source code must be accessible at no charge through a publicly
reachable network location.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Mandatory Attribution Requirement

Any Interface displaying or providing access to a Digital Product
Passport generated, processed, or served using this Software or any
Derivative Work must display the following notice:

    Powered by Open-Label.eu

The notice must:

1. Be visible to end users accessing the Digital Product Passport.
2. Appear on the same page or interface where the Digital Product
   Passport content is displayed.
3. Include a hyperlink to:

    https://open-label.eu

The notice must not be hidden, minimized, obscured, or rendered
invisible through styling, scripting, or other technical means.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Prohibition on Removal of Attribution

You may not remove, modify, or obscure the attribution notice required
by Section 4 while continuing to use any portion of the Software.

Removing the attribution while using the Software or any Derivative Work
constitutes a violation of this License.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

6. Forks and Modified Versions

You may create forks or derivative works of the Software.

However, any fork that continues to use the Software codebase must
comply with the attribution requirements of Section 4.

If you wish to remove the attribution requirement, you must remove all
Open-Label Software code and reimplement the functionality independently.

